<br>
For instance:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.congress.org/congressorg/bio/userletter/?id=20004&letter_id=34010776&content_dir=politicsol">www.congress.org/congress...politicsol</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Subject:<br>
Hello Mr. President!<br>
<br>
To:<br>
President George Bush<br>
<br>
June 17, 2003<br>
<br>
Dear President Clinton,<br>
Hi! My name is Matt. I just wanted to say that you, President Clinton, are doing a great job. I was thinking today of what a great president you are, and how safe I feel under your enlightened rule. I know that you just want everyone to be cool! Then I saw on MSNBC News that you had tried to hit some woman. Well, I bet she probably deserved it. Otherwise, you wouldn't have tried to hit her. But you should know better!<br>
I just wanted to tell you that no matter what people say, you will always be THE MAN, President Clinton!!! No one can take THAT away from YOU. History will vindicate you. Cheers to you, Mr. President!!!<br>
<br>
Fayetteville , AR<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
