<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.congress.org/congressorg/bio/userletter/?id=20004&letter_id=34296776">www.congress.org/congress...d=34296776</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Habitual Liars Association Supports George Bush<br>
<br>
To:<br>
President George Bush<br>
<br>
June 18, 2003<br>
<br>
As President of the Habitual Liars Association,(actually I'm just the corresponding secretary) I want to congratulate you on your stellar representation of liars everywhere. Not since the days when Lyndon Johnson lied about the nonexistant Gulf of Tonkin incident and got 50,000 Americans killed in Vietnam has lying been so effectively executed by an American President. You should be proud!<br>
<br>
I know that con and scam artists everywhere feel a little more self-esteem these days with you in office. You are an inspiration to all of us. Keep up the good work!<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
<br>
Richard M. Nixon<br>
<br>
Past President of the United States<br>
Former living person.<br>
<br>
Prevaricator's Point , IL<br>
